The paper deals with image segmentation using a convolutional neural network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of raw pixels instead of preprocessing steps suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with historical document images, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
